.Dd $Mdocdate: July 25 2011 $
.Dt WCSLEN 3
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm wcslen
.Nd find length of a wide string
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.In wchar.h
.Ft size_t
.Fn wcslen "const wchar_t *s"
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Fn wcslen
function computes the length of the wide string
.Fa s .
.Sh RETURN VALUES
The
.Fn wcslen
function returns the number of wide characters that precede the terminating
null wide character.
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr strlen 3 ,
.Xr wcswidth 3
.Sh STANDARDS
The
.Fn wcslen
function conforms to
.St -isoC-99
and was first introduced in
.St -isoC-amd1 .
.Sh HISTORY
The
.Fn wcslen
function was ported from
.Nx
and first appeared in
.Ox 3.8 .
@


